name: BleedingAtNonCriticalSite
title: Bleeding at Non Critical Site
description: The intent of the measure that this value set was created for is focused on bleeding that is likely to be etiologically related to in-hospital use of pharmacoprophylaxis for venous thromboembolism.  This concept of bleeding at non-critical sites is to count bleeding events that may result in a decrease in hemoglobin or transfusion, but do not lead to loss of important functions due to their anatomic location.
purpose: (Clinical Focus: The purpose of this Grouped value set is to identify major bleeding events not involving a critical area or organ during an encounter.),(Data Element Scope: This value set may use a model element related to Diagnosis.),(Inclusion Criteria: Includes concepts that represent diagnoses that indicate new onset of bleeding not involving a critical area or organ.),(Exclusion Criteria: Excludes concepts that represent any bleeding diagnoses that involve critical areas or organs.  Injury or traumatic causes of bleeding are excluded. Obstetric related bleeds are also excluded.)
